[BID 4S] ⟦You complete the transfer by bidding 4\S, the suit partner asked for.⟧ Now your partner bids 4NT, Roman Key Card Blackwood agreeing spades and asking for the five keycards — the four aces plus the king of trumps. Under 1430 the steps are: 5\C = one or four, 5\D = zero or three, 5\H = two without the trump queen, 5\S = two with it.
[BID 5C] ⟦You answer 5\C, showing one or four keycards — here, one.⟧ Hearing the keycards add up, your partner bids the slam, 6\S.
[BID Pass] ⟦You pass; 6\S is the final contract.⟧
[show NS]South opened 1NT with \ST7 \HKJ87 \DKQ7 \CAQ64 — a balanced 15 — completed the Texas transfer to 4\S, and a single keycard answer let responder bid 6\S. Texas then RKC put the trump suit and the slam decision in responder's hands while keeping the strong notrump hidden.}
